cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SI, cs.AI, cs.CV

The paper proposes a framework for joint embedding of structural and functional brain networks using graph convolutions and Siamese architecture. This involves learning representations from two different types of brain networks, which suggests the paper could belong to sub-categories such as machine learning (cs.LG), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), social and information networks (cs.SI), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV). Among these, cs.LG and cs.NE are the most likely categories as they are directly related to the proposed approach of using graph convolutions and Siamese architecture for learning joint embeddings. The other categories are also possible as they are relevant to the application domain of brain networks and could be used to further refine the approach or evaluate its performance.
